cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.IT 

This paper focuses on the networking infrastructure challenges of VR 360-degree videos, which falls under the category of networked and internet-based systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the technical requirements for achieving the ultimate VR 360 experience, which involves multimedia processing (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also considers the user experience and safety concerns of wireless access to VR 360 services, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different wireless technologies, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
